244
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:50.360
- Tried to get him to make the right call…
- Oh. babe. Isaiah.

245
00:17:51.111 --> 00:17:53.072
I'm so sorry.

246
00:17:54.073 --> 00:17:55.115
Oh…

247
00:17:55.991 --> 00:17:59.119
You always want these men
to make different decisions.

248
00:17:59.661 --> 00:18:02.498
But not everybody's built like you. babe.

249
00:18:02.581 --> 00:18:05.459
The little girl. Paola.
she's back home with her father.

250
00:18:05.542 --> 00:18:09.797
Some big-time cartel guy. But. you know.
it's not her fault who her daddy is.

251
00:18:12.132 --> 00:18:14.551
How do you know that about her father.
but not about your own?

252
00:18:15.135 --> 00:18:16.720
His behavior's not your fault.

253
00:18:17.304 --> 00:18:19.306
But you can't help taking it on.

254
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:23.685
Listen. Dr. Stiles.
this session's been great.

255
00:18:23.769 --> 00:18:26.688
but I can no longer afford the copay. so…

256
00:18:26.772 --> 00:18:30.109
You can't afford to keep treating our son
like your father treated you.

257
00:18:30.192 --> 00:18:31.318
I ain't like that nigga.

258
00:18:31.401 --> 00:18:34.404
Different reason to run the streets.
different reason to own a gun.

259
00:18:34.488 --> 00:18:35.614
Same working hours.

260
00:18:35.697 --> 00:18:37.991
Candace. I never lied to you
about who I am.

261
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:39.284
- You had options.
- Oh boy.

262
00:18:39.368 --> 00:18:42.496
You could've picked the suit.
Could've been Mrs. Uptight Motherfucker.

263
00:18:42.579 --> 00:18:45.791
You and Malik aren't as different
from each other as you think.

264
00:18:45.874 --> 00:18:47.960
But back in college. I didn't want him.

265
00:18:48.544 --> 00:18:49.878
I wanted you.

266
00:18:51.797 --> 00:18:53.882
I want you.

267
00:18:56.426 --> 00:18:57.678
On time.

268
00:18:59.596 --> 00:19:00.430
Baby.

269
00:19:02.307 --> 00:19:05.144
We can keep having
the same conversation over and over.

270
00:19:05.227 --> 00:19:06.728
but it's never gonna go any different.

271
00:19:06.812 --> 00:19:08.605
Can we skip to the end already?

272
00:19:08.689 --> 00:19:11.608
Eat this incredible meal you prepared.

273
00:19:11.692 --> 00:19:13.026
Enjoy ourselves.

274
00:19:14.486 --> 00:19:15.571
Sure.

275
00:19:16.113 --> 00:19:17.489
It's getting late.

276
00:19:18.657 --> 00:19:20.284
- Let me heat up the chicken.
- Okay.

277
00:19:23.245 --> 00:19:24.621
I'll go wash up.

278
00:19:27.249 --> 00:19:29.334
Happy anniversary. by the way.

279
00:19:47.978 --> 00:19:49.479
- Hey.
- Hi.

280
00:19:49.563 --> 00:19:51.732
Tonight.
I feel like celebrating.

281
00:19:51.815 --> 00:19:54.109
Cash take was 1.7 million.

282
00:19:55.110 --> 00:19:56.778
Wouldn't have happened without you.

283
00:19:56.862 --> 00:19:58.947
Everything went off without a hitch.

284
00:19:59.031 --> 00:20:00.616
All five of us.

285
00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:03.368
We got in. We got out. Clean.

286
00:20:04.244 --> 00:20:06.788
You were amazing last night.
You didn't miss a beat.

287
00:20:08.540 --> 00:20:11.001
Felt good being in the moment with you.

288
00:20:11.084 --> 00:20:12.794
Two of us. as a team again.

289
00:20:13.503 --> 00:20:14.880
Like we were before.

290
00:20:14.963 --> 00:20:18.342
Yeah. um. Coltrane. about last night.

291
00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:21.845
I can't do that again.

292
00:20:23.222 --> 00:20:24.848
I was terrified.

293
00:20:24.932 --> 00:20:26.808
When you didn't
come through the door on time…

294
00:20:26.892 --> 00:20:27.851
I was only seconds off.

295
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:31.021
Exactly. and if you'd run
into a real problem. I just…

296
00:20:31.104 --> 00:20:32.773
But I didn't. And I won't.

297
00:20:32.856 --> 00:20:35.067
You can't promise me that.

298
00:20:38.695 --> 00:20:39.696
Look.

299
00:20:43.992 --> 00:20:47.079
When we lost Zahir…

300
00:20:49.623 --> 00:20:51.333
something inside me changed.

301
00:20:53.543 --> 00:20:56.296
I just don't feel the way I used to feel.

302
00:20:58.757 --> 00:21:01.510
Look. I want you to think
about what we said.

303
00:21:02.219 --> 00:21:04.846
Remember we said we'd be out
once we had the baby?

304
00:21:04.930 --> 00:21:09.142
We'd live a normal life.
not looking over our shoulders anymore?

305
00:21:09.226 --> 00:21:10.894
That was our dream.

306
00:21:11.645 --> 00:21:12.521
Mm-hmm.

307
00:21:13.647 --> 00:21:15.148
We may not have our son.

308
00:21:15.232 --> 00:21:17.818
but I'm not willing to let go
of that part of the dream.

309
00:21:19.528 --> 00:21:20.821
Okay.

310
00:21:25.742 --> 00:21:27.369
The guys are hungry. Ebony.

311
00:21:28.161 --> 00:21:29.371
I have to make them whole.

312
00:21:29.454 --> 00:21:32.791
We had March. but last night was only
the second job that we had this year.

313
00:21:38.297 --> 00:21:40.841
Two more jobs. Two more jobs. that's it.

314
00:21:40.924 --> 00:21:43.260
You and I can focus
on our future together.

315
00:21:45.012 --> 00:21:46.263
Do you mean that?

316
00:21:48.598 --> 00:21:49.766
I love you. Ebony.

317
00:21:50.684 --> 00:21:51.852
I love you too.

318
00:21:54.813 --> 00:21:56.023
Come here.

319
00:21:58.900 --> 00:22:00.402
You're so beautiful.

320
00:22:01.486 --> 00:22:05.240
Do you wanna go upstairs
and work up an appetite?

321
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:08.160
I thought you'd never ask.

322
00:22:40.275 --> 00:22:41.526
Candace. baby.

323
00:22:42.235 --> 00:22:43.612
This was delicious.

324
00:22:44.696 --> 00:22:48.325
Mm. Well. I only cook twice a year.
so I'm glad it was edible at least.

325
00:22:51.870 --> 00:22:54.998
Hey. we don't have
to clean up right away. You know?

326
00:22:56.625 --> 00:22:57.918
Good night. Isaiah.

327
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:06.927
All right.

328
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:15.477
Good night. Candace.

329
00:23:57.018 --> 00:23:59.521
Oh. shit.

330
00:25:32.572 --> 00:25:34.199
Breakfast is in the oven.

331
00:25:38.912 --> 00:25:39.996
Thanks. Dad.

332
00:25:41.373 --> 00:25:43.542
- Hey. grab mine too. yeah?
- Yeah.

333
00:25:45.710 --> 00:25:47.420
How was your game yesterday?

334
00:25:48.713 --> 00:25:49.756
It was cool.

335
00:25:50.465 --> 00:25:52.300
I had ten points.

336
00:25:53.510 --> 00:25:54.844
- Three rebounds.
- Okay.

337
00:25:54.928 --> 00:25:56.846
Five assists. though.

338
00:25:56.930 --> 00:25:58.265
And a steal.

339
00:25:58.348 --> 00:26:00.725
Hey. good game. son.

340
00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:01.851
Yeah.

341
00:26:02.561 --> 00:26:06.731
Uh… would've been cool
if you had come through. though.

342
00:26:09.234 --> 00:26:12.028
I saw your next home game
on the calendar. I'll be there.

343
00:26:13.196 --> 00:26:14.281
Sure.

344
00:26:16.074 --> 00:26:17.617
I'm giving you my word.

345
00:26:18.159 --> 00:26:20.954
That shit means something. I'll be there.

346
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:25.584
Noah. go get ready for school.

347
00:26:26.501 --> 00:26:28.753
- Can I…?
- Yeah.

348
00:26:30.088 --> 00:26:33.300
Oh. look at Mom with the drip. huh?

349
00:26:41.433 --> 00:26:42.726
Thanks for making breakfast.

350
00:26:42.809 --> 00:26:45.228
Yeah. my pancakes are better than yours.

351
00:26:51.943 --> 00:26:55.322
I'm sorry. Isaiah. about last night.

352
00:26:56.197 --> 00:26:58.617
I wouldn't have taken that tone if…

353
00:26:59.618 --> 00:27:01.703
Why didn't you just tell me
you remembered?

354
00:27:02.704 --> 00:27:07.542
I had a different idea…
of how things would go.

355
00:27:09.419 --> 00:27:12.005
I hate we're like this. I…

356
00:27:13.256 --> 00:27:15.342
- I hate it this way.
- I know.

357
00:27:25.560 --> 00:27:28.480
Oh. Isaiah. wow.

358
00:27:35.570 --> 00:27:37.614
I miss this.

359
00:27:40.700 --> 00:27:42.202
Babe…

360
00:27:47.749 --> 00:27:48.708
It's Jimmy.

361
00:27:53.797 --> 00:27:56.424
I gotta take it.

362
00:28:01.930 --> 00:28:04.182
I guess I should get Noah to school.

363
00:28:13.733 --> 00:28:15.568
- Yeah?
- Morning. sunshine.

364
00:28:15.652 --> 00:28:16.736
We need to meet.

365
00:28:18.530 --> 00:28:19.447
Yeah.

366
00:28:22.617 --> 00:28:26.329
You're not on the Halloween case.
But here's the file.

367
00:28:28.081 --> 00:28:30.458
There's nothing there says
it's the guys you're looking for.

368
00:28:30.542 --> 00:28:33.002
If there's security footage.
you'll get it for me. right?

369
00:28:33.086 --> 00:28:36.798
- I'm gonna catch these motherfuckers.
- You ain't. There's no them to catch.

370
00:28:36.881 --> 00:28:39.426
And when you don't manifest
these imaginary motherfuckers.

371
00:28:39.509 --> 00:28:41.553
you're gonna ruin your rep
because you sound crazy.

372
00:28:41.636 --> 00:28:44.347
Or lose your goddamn badge
because you do something crazy.

373
00:28:44.431 --> 00:28:46.474
I know what this shit is about. Isaiah.

374
00:28:46.558 --> 00:28:48.810
What happened with Detective Shaw
was a goddamn tragedy.

375
00:28:48.893 --> 00:28:52.313
But we caught the son of a bitch
responsible two years ago.

376
00:28:52.397 --> 00:28:53.815
Tyrell Pope didn't kill Shaw.

377
00:28:53.898 --> 00:28:57.944
We caught Pope with the murder weapon
in the same jacket as the suspect.

378
00:28:58.027 --> 00:29:00.447
And he had the keys
to the distro in his possession.

379
00:29:00.530 --> 00:29:04.451
It was handed to us. Jimmy.
On a fucking platter. and we just took it.

380
00:29:04.534 --> 00:29:05.952
Let it go!

381
00:29:07.787 --> 00:29:08.788
It's over.

382
00:29:10.206 --> 00:29:12.000
I'm vouching for you with the brass.

383
00:29:12.083 --> 00:29:13.334
You need to go for captain.

384
00:29:14.043 --> 00:29:16.796
Be home for dinner every night.

385
00:29:17.714 --> 00:29:19.382
See your son.

386
00:29:28.725 --> 00:29:30.268
- Boom.
- All right.

387
00:29:30.351 --> 00:29:32.395
- We good now?
- We are more than good.

388
00:29:32.479 --> 00:29:37.734
Wilder Holdings is now the proud owner
of its 15th shopping center in LA.

389
00:29:37.817 --> 00:29:41.029
And this one's actually in your name.
No. uh. shell company this time?

390
00:29:41.112 --> 00:29:43.281
I wanna keep this one on the books. Sam.

391
00:29:43.364 --> 00:29:47.076
Ebony and I plan on keeping this property
in the community for the community.

392
00:29:47.160 --> 00:29:48.828
Mm-hmm.

393
00:29:51.623 --> 00:29:53.958
Is that the old Magic Johnson Theater?

394
00:29:54.042 --> 00:29:56.669
My. my. how the neighborhood has changed.

395
00:29:56.753 --> 00:29:57.587
Amazing.

396
00:29:57.670 --> 00:29:58.880
Charlie. what's up?

397
00:29:59.881 --> 00:30:02.759
I have that for you.
I'm just finishing up some business.

398
00:30:04.761 --> 00:30:05.887
I'll see you there.

399
00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:30.537
Welcome back. Coltrane.

400
00:30:30.620 --> 00:30:32.163
170K.

401
00:30:32.247 --> 00:30:34.207
Your cut from the Halloween job.

402
00:30:34.290 --> 00:30:36.167
You can come in now. Tanya.

403
00:30:40.755 --> 00:30:41.923
Miss Tinker Bell.

404
00:30:43.299 --> 00:30:45.343
- You did good in there.
- Pleasure working with you.

405
00:30:53.101 --> 00:30:56.229
Diamonds may be a girl's best friend.
but cash is for grown-ass women.

406
00:30:57.522 --> 00:31:00.358
Now. speaking of grown-ass women.
how's my little sister? She good?

407
00:31:00.441 --> 00:31:03.361
- Getting back to work?
- Ebony was amazing on Halloween.

408
00:31:03.444 --> 00:31:04.779
Just like old times. Charlie.

409
00:31:04.863 --> 00:31:06.364
I'm glad to hear it.

410
00:31:06.990 --> 00:31:10.326
Even though the two of you
can stop this double-life shit any time.

411
00:31:10.410 --> 00:31:13.079
You can walk. You got enough money.

412
00:31:13.162 --> 00:31:15.373
There's never enough
when it comes to money.

413
00:31:17.166 --> 00:31:19.294
My crew went hungry while we were down.

414
00:31:19.961 --> 00:31:22.297
They need to work.
which means I need another job.

415
00:31:22.380 --> 00:31:25.008
So. I hope that file
is exactly what I think it is.

416
00:31:26.885 --> 00:31:31.306
Six million in untraceable diamonds.
We'll take down 50 cents on the dollar.

417
00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:33.391
So. three million bucks.

418
00:31:34.851 --> 00:31:37.437
- Schematics?
- Downtown. Jewelry district.

419
00:31:37.520 --> 00:31:40.273
Front for a money-laundering crew.
But there's a hurdle.

420
00:31:40.356 --> 00:31:42.025
Stones are being held in 3 different safes

421
00:31:42.108 --> 00:31:44.694
at three different stores back-to-back
on the same block.

422
00:31:44.777 --> 00:31:47.071
It's not a hurdle.
That's a gauntlet. Charlie.

423
00:31:47.572 --> 00:31:48.573
What's the timeline?

424
00:31:48.656 --> 00:31:51.534
According to my source.
the stones will be gone in two weeks.

425
00:31:51.618 --> 00:31:53.161
They're being held in even splits.

426
00:31:53.244 --> 00:31:56.831
If you wanna ensure max payout.
you're gonna have to hit all three stores.

427
00:31:59.375 --> 00:32:00.710
Mm-hmm.

428
00:32:03.379 --> 00:32:06.424
Charlie. I'd like Ebony
to sit this one out.

429
00:32:09.135 --> 00:32:11.804
- I got someone who can handle it.
- All right.

430
00:32:12.305 --> 00:32:15.934
Ebony needs you. Coltrane.
Come back from this shit in one piece.

431
00:32:18.436 --> 00:32:21.648
- You better keep your word with me.
- I never break my word.

432
00:32:21.731 --> 00:32:23.441
Not to you. and not to Ebony.

433
00:32:24.651 --> 00:32:25.652
She's all I have. Charlie.

434
00:32:26.819 --> 00:32:27.946
Same here.

435
00:32:33.826 --> 00:32:35.203
Expect my call.

436
00:32:44.170 --> 00:32:45.380
On my momma. momma.

437
00:32:45.463 --> 00:32:47.799
The Clippers can't never cover
a nigga's spread. Not never.

438
00:32:47.882 --> 00:32:49.550
- What the fuck?
- Focus up. Deon.

439
00:32:49.634 --> 00:32:52.261
We need you fully present here.
We only got two weeks. gentlemen.

440
00:32:52.345 --> 00:32:54.430
Two weeks?
That's faster than we usually move.

441
00:32:54.514 --> 00:32:56.099
You wanted work. right?

442
00:32:56.182 --> 00:32:57.392
Here it is.

443
00:32:57.475 --> 00:33:00.728
Untraceable stones. Three locations.

444
00:33:00.812 --> 00:33:03.690
- Even amounts in each.
- So we gotta hit all three.

445
00:33:03.773 --> 00:33:05.149
If I'm looking at this right.

446
00:33:05.233 --> 00:33:07.694
when we get to a third store.
they'll be expecting us.

447
00:33:07.777 --> 00:33:09.696
Bang. bang. My kids need a new daddy.

448
00:33:09.779 --> 00:33:13.866
Yeah. well. the way I see it.
there's only one way to get this job done.

449
00:33:32.927 --> 00:33:33.970
Fuck!

450
00:33:43.104 --> 00:33:45.231
Our boss
would like a word with you.

451
00:33:51.696 --> 00:33:53.740
Do you know who I am.
Lieutenant Stiles?

452
00:33:54.907 --> 00:33:56.492
Miguel Alvarez.

453
00:33:56.576 --> 00:33:57.660
Viejo Cartel.

454
00:34:00.288 --> 00:34:02.248
My family is very grateful
for what you did.

455
00:34:06.919 --> 00:34:10.214
I'm having a small dispute
about territory.

456
00:34:10.298 --> 00:34:12.216
and things have escalated.

457
00:34:13.092 --> 00:34:15.762
And you saving my daughter
from those animals…

458
00:34:17.138 --> 00:34:19.682
You have to pardon me. Lieutenant.
I'm not used to thanking cops.

459
00:34:19.766 --> 00:34:20.808
This is all brand-new.

460
00:34:23.144 --> 00:34:26.064
I would offer you cash
as a token of my appreciation.

461
00:34:26.147 --> 00:34:28.691
- I ain't taking shit from you.
- Exactamente.

462
00:34:28.775 --> 00:34:31.527
And judging by the way
you killed that one mamón.

463
00:34:31.611 --> 00:34:32.528
I would hire you.

464
00:34:32.612 --> 00:34:34.655
You know the answer to that too.

465
00:34:34.739 --> 00:34:37.325
So if I can't pay you
and I can't hire you.

466
00:34:37.408 --> 00:34:39.243
all I can offer you is this.

467
00:34:40.536 --> 00:34:45.541
If there's anything you ever need
that falls outside of your…

468
00:34:46.876 --> 00:34:48.503
official purview.

469
00:34:49.420 --> 00:34:50.463
contact me.

470
00:34:53.466 --> 00:34:56.302
- So you owe me now?
- If that's how you wanna put it.

471
00:34:56.385 --> 00:34:59.722
Negocio es negocio. Business is business.

472
00:35:01.474 --> 00:35:02.558
Ernesto!

473
00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:20.827
I executed the plan on Halloween.
but my heart was pounding.

474
00:35:20.910 --> 00:35:22.286
I felt like I was gonna faint.

475
00:35:22.370 --> 00:35:25.623
And so what?
That's when training and instinct kick in.

476
00:35:25.706 --> 00:35:28.709
People either have it or they don't.
and you have it in spades.

477
00:35:28.793 --> 00:35:30.419
No. I had it.

478
00:35:30.503 --> 00:35:32.630
I'm not going back out there. Charlie.
I'm done.

479
00:35:32.713 --> 00:35:35.758
Maybe you weren't ready yet.
You'll feel better next time.

480
00:35:35.842 --> 00:35:37.718
There's not gonna be a next time.

481
00:35:38.636 --> 00:35:41.139
- Coltrane and I have a dream.
- You livin' the dream.

482
00:35:41.222 --> 00:35:44.100
You know how many girls want to find
Black fucking Prince Charming?

483
00:35:44.183 --> 00:35:46.602
- Get the house. the car. all that.
- Not you.

484
00:35:46.686 --> 00:35:47.728
Hell no.

485
00:35:49.730 --> 00:35:51.315
But you wanted that man. and I agreed.

486
00:35:51.399 --> 00:35:54.443
He said he was going to build up
real estate business. pay taxes.

487
00:35:54.527 --> 00:35:57.280
and make you look like an honest woman.

488
00:35:57.363 --> 00:35:59.323
But I didn't want you to be one.

489
00:36:00.074 --> 00:36:02.910
Ivy League. you're criminally minded.
You almost as smart as me.

490
00:36:02.994 --> 00:36:05.121
A couple more scores.
you'll be back the way you were.

491
00:36:05.204 --> 00:36:07.456
I don't think I'll ever be the way I was.

492
00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:10.376
I just woke up one day.
and Zahir was gone.

493
00:36:10.459 --> 00:36:14.797
That feeling of him
